snippet.textDisplay: That’s actually called cleithrophobia not claustrophobia. Cleithrophobia is the fear of being trapped, so even if you’re in a tight space you are ok if you can get out. On the other hand, you may be in the open, but if you can’t move you’re still scared. I know because I have it and was curious :)
